{"name":"Tradixo","permalink":"tradixo","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/company/tradixo","homepage_url":"http://tradixo.com/home","blog_url":"http://tradixo.tumblr.com/","blog_feed_url":"","twitter_username":"tradixo","category_code":"web","number_of_employees":2,"founded_year":2011,"founded_month":8,"founded_day":1,"deadpooled_year":null,"deadpooled_month":null,"deadpooled_day":null,"deadpooled_url":null,"tag_list":"translation, language, game, social, network, community","alias_list":null,"email_address":"contact@tradixo.com","phone_number":"+33 629 761 841","description":"community based on translation exchange","created_at":"Tue Aug 21 19:15:34 UTC 2012","updated_at":"Thu Aug 23 18:28:49 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>Tradixo is a social translation platform:</p>\n\n<p>Each user is given 10 credits at registration. One credit allow a user to ask for one translation. On the other hand, providing a transaltion will allow the user to earn a credit.</p>\n\n<p>When someone asks for a translation, it will be sent to every user who is native in the target language. When one of these natives provide a translation, this translation is displayed to the asker but also sent back to the community to be voted. In the end, the asker can receive several translation from native people, the number of vote per translation giving an estimation of the transaltion&#8217;s quality.</p>\n\n<p>Users who ask for translations have the ability to check the profile of their translators and reward them. The more a user is rewarded, the higher his reputation will be, allowing him to level up, earn gifts and finally be paid for long text translations.</p>\n\n<p>In other words Tradixo is a way to bring down language barriers while having fun!</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,48],"assets/images/resized/0020/7294/207294v2-max-150x150.jpg"],[[213,69],"assets/images/resized/0020/7294/207294v2-max-250x250.jpg"],[[213,69],"assets/images/resized/0020/7294/207294v2-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attri